==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Poltroon
<hw>Pol*troon"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>poltron</ets>, from It. <ets>poltrone</ets> an idle fellow,
sluggard, coward, <ets>poltro</ets> idle, lazy, also, bed, fr. OHG.
<ets>polstar</ets>, <ets>bolstar</ets>, cushion, G. <ets>polster</ets>,
akin to E. <ets>bolster</ets>. See <er>Bolster</er>.]</ety> <def>An
arrant coward; a dastard; a craven; a mean-spirited wretch.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poltroon</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Poltroon
<hw>Pol*troon"</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Base; vile; contemptible;
cowardly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

